"Ibreighith M., Fiebig M., Leipertz A., Wu G.","Thermal Diffusivity of the Alternative Refrigerants R123, R134a, R142b and R152a in the Liquid Phase",1992,"Fluid Phase Equilibria","80","C",,"323","332",,,10.1016/0378-3812(92)87078-2,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0026946210&partnerID=40&md5=8a6b4265798bf4ce19bdcada4027831d","Ruhr-Universitat Bochum, Institut für Thermo- und Fluiddynamik, Postfach 10 21 48, 46SO Bochum 1, Germany; Friedrich Alexander Universität Erlangen-Nümberg, Am Weichselgarten 9, 8520 Erlangen, Germany","Ibreighith, M., Ruhr-Universitat Bochum, Institut für Thermo- und Fluiddynamik, Postfach 10 21 48, 46SO Bochum 1, Germany; Fiebig, M., Friedrich Alexander Universität Erlangen-Nümberg, Am Weichselgarten 9, 8520 Erlangen, Germany; Leipertz, A., Friedrich Alexander Universität Erlangen-Nümberg, Am Weichselgarten 9, 8520 Erlangen, Germany; Wu, G., Ruhr-Universitat Bochum, Institut für Thermo- und Fluiddynamik, Postfach 10 21 48, 46SO Bochum 1, Germany","The thermal diffusivity of the refrigerants 1,1-dichloro-2,2,2-trifluoroethane (R123), 1,1,1,2-tetrafluoroethane (R134a), 1,1-difluoroethane (R152a) and 1-chloro-1,1-difluoroethane (R142b) with low ozone depletion potential (ODP) and low global warming potential (GWP) has been measured at different pressures in a wide temperature range below the critical point. These substances are proposed as substitutes for the traditional refrigerants especially R123 for R11, R134a and R152a for R12 and R142b for R114. The measurements were carried out using the photon correlation spectroscopy (PCS). The measured values of the thermal diffusivity are presented as a function of temperature and compared with those of the traditional refrigerants. The thermal diffusivities of the possible substitutes can be up to 70% higher or lower than the traditional refrigerants. © 1992.","alternative refrigerant; global warming potential; light scattering; ozone depletion potential; photon correlation spectroscopy; R11; R114; R12; R123; R134a; R142b; R152a; thermal diffusivity","Fluorocarbons; Freons; Ozone layer; Thermal diffusion in liquids; Thermal variables measurement; Alternative refrigerants; Global warming; Ozone depletion; Thermal diffusivity measurement; Refrigerants",,,,,,"Baehr, H.D. 1990. private comunication. Universität Hannover, Institut für Thermodynamik, Callinstraße 36, 3000 Hannover 1Chu, (1974) Laser Light Scattering, , Academic Press, New York; Du Pont 1987. Fluorkohlenstoff/OzonFiebig, Ibreghith, Pitz-Paal, Leipertz, Wu, Determination of thermal and mass diffusivity by photon correlation spectroscopy. Paper presented at “Thermal properties of pure substances and mixtures for refrigeration”. (1990) Int. Inst. Refrigeration (IRR), , March 5–7. 1990 in Dan Accadia, Herzlia, Israel; Graßl, H. Einfluß von FCKW-Kältemitteln auf die Temperaturstruktur der Atmosphäre und das Klima. FCKW-Symposium, 2. Juli 1987, Fa. Bahr StuttgartHendrix, Leipertz, Fiebig, Simonsohn, Thermal diifusivity of transparent liquids by photon correlation spectroscopy-I (1987) Int. J. Heat Mass Transfer, 30, pp. 333-339. , Results for toluene and methanol in an extended range of temperature and pressure; Hesse, Kruse, Das FCKW-Problem für die Kältetechnik (1988) Klima - Kälte - Heizung, p. 4; Ibreighith, M. to be publishedLeipertz, Hendrix, Fiebig, Wu, Spectroscopic determination of the thermal diffusivities of some pure transparent organic liquids (1984) VDI-Ber., pp. 163-179. , Nr. 539; Leipertz, Wu, Fiebig, Spectroscopic determination of the thermal diffusivity of organic mixtures and refrigerants (1987) Heat and Mass Transfer in Refrigeration and Cryogenics, pp. 392-403. , J. Bougard, N. Afgan, Hemisphere Publ. Corp; Reile, Jany, Straub, Messung der Temperaturleitfähigkeit reiner Fluide and binärer Gemische mit Hilfe der dynamischen Lichtstreuung (1984) Wärme- und Stoffübertr., 18, pp. 99-108; Wu, Fiebig, Leipertz, Thermal diffusivity of transparent liquids by photon correlat